<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; page-break-before: always">
<FONT SIZE=6 STYLE="font-size: 22pt"><B>NTP - Survey 2005</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT SIZE=5><B>Contact:</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><FONT SIZE=3>Pedro
Torres - torres at pop-pr.rnp.br</FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"> 
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT SIZE=5><B>What?</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The NTP Survey 2005 is
a data collect and analysis from the NTP network. A previous NTP
survey and results can be found at:</P>
<UL>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<FONT SIZE=3><A HREF="http://www.media.mit.edu/~nelson/research/ntp-survey99/">http://www.media.mit.edu/~nelson/research/ntp-survey99/</A></FONT></P>
</UL>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT SIZE=5><B>Where?</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The IP addresses that
will scan the NTP network is 200.238.131.1 and 2001:12f0:100:7::2 whose owner is PoP-PR
(point of presence of Brazilian Network Research in Paran&aacute;).
The reverse DNS for this address is ntpsurvey.arauc.br.</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><FONT SIZE=3>This
suggestion has been made to NTP Survey 1999 by Nelson Minar. The
purpose is that when an administrator notices an access coming from
IP address above he can reach this web page (<A HREF="http://www.ntpsurvey.arauc.br/">www.ntpsurvey.arauc.br</A>)
with information regarding the survey.</FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT SIZE=5><B>When?</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The expected time to
scan the entire NTP network is roughly 5 weeks and should start on
08/30/2005. During this period your server may receive one or more
queries which responses will be used for statistical analysis only.
It won't compromise your network nor NTP server. This scan is not
related to any security hole in NTP servers.</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><FONT SIZE=3>The
summarized data and possibly a paper will be available this year here
(I think!) :)</FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT SIZE=5><B>How?</B></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The basic idea of NTP
survey 2005 is to collect data in all hosts avaliable for public
access of the NTP network using a program developed with that
objective.</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The list of available
hosts in the NTP network is incremented querying each host previously
known which peers recently queried them.</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The most important data
we are looking for:</P>
<UL>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The current time;</P>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The delay to
	communicate with the peer;</P>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The difference
	between the peer's time and hosts' own (offset);</P>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The estimated
	error of the peer's clock and root time server (dispersion);</P>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The distance (in
	seconds) to the root time server;</P>
	<LI><P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The version of NTP
	protocol;</P>
</UL>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm">The command that will
be executed for each host is:</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Courier, monospace"><FONT SIZE=2>&gt;
ntpdc -n -c sysinfo -c peers -c monlist &lt;IP ADDRESS&gt;</FONT></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><FONT FACE="Courier,
monospace"><FONT SIZE=2>&gt;
ntpq -n -c as -c rv "assid" &lt;IP ADDRESS&gt;</FONT></FONT></P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm"><BR>
</P>
<P CLASS="western" STYLE="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: medium"><BR>
